article.headline: Missouri 72, Nebraska 51
article.story:
LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Drew Snyder scored 19 points to lead four
players in double figures as Nebraska-Wesleyan defeated the
University of Sioux Falls 80-68 on Saturday in the Great Plains
Athletic Conference.

Ben Biehl added 15 points, Wyatt Schmidt 13 and Matt Harms had
10 for Nebraska-Wesleyan (11-7, 8-5 Great Plains Athletic
Conference).

Steve Esselink scored a game-high 21 points to lead Sioux Falls
(16-10, 8-5 GPAC). J.D. Roberts chipped in 12 points and had seven
rebounds.
